H0.text: The foxtrot, a dance introduced to Great Britain around 1914, originated in which country. Canada

H1.text: The foxtrot, a dance introduced to Great Britain around 1914, originated in which country. Australia

H2.text: The foxtrot, a dance introduced to Great Britain around 1914, originated in which country. Germany

H3.text: The foxtrot, a dance introduced to Great Britain around 1914, originated in which country. US

A4.text: The foxtrot was originally danced to ragtime.

A5.text: Two sources, Vernon Castle and dance teacher Betty Lee, credit African American dancers as the source of the foxtrot.
